{"title":"Boring Wheelset? Chris King’s New Anodized Centerlock Lock Rings are the Solution","link":"https://bikerumor.com/boring-wheelset-chris-kings-new-anodized-centerlock-lock-rings-are-the-solution/","date":1743602400000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-hero.webp\" width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" alt=\"(Photos / Chris King)\" /></p>\n<p>Portland, Oregon’s <a href=\"http://chrisking.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Chris King Precision Components</a> makes some of the best hubs in the biz. And when you purchase a set of their Centerlock hubs, you’ll normally just get a Shimano Centerlock ring with it. If that little essential Shimano part is too boring for you, now you can add a splash of color with a new Chris King anodized Centerlock lockring. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>New King rings may also be the answer, if you just have some other less shiny ho-hum wheelset that needs sprucing up…</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Chris King Centerlock alloy Lock Rings in pretty colors</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-first-pic-e1743521114254.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"777\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-first-pic-e1743521114254.webp\" alt=\"Chris King Centerlock Lockrings first pic\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-first-pic-e1743521114254.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-first-pic-e1743521114254-297x180.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-first-pic-e1743521114254-120x73.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-first-pic-e1743521114254-768x466.webp 768w\" /></a><figcaption><em>(Photos / Chris King)</em></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The only question you’ll be asking yourself is: “<em>Do I match the rest of my steed’s color theme, or be bold and add some contrast with these lil’ unsung heroes of the stopping world?</em>“</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-contrast-e1743521163376.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"813\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-contrast-e1743521163376.webp\" alt=\"Chris King Centerlock Lockrings contrast\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-contrast-e1743521163376.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-contrast-e1743521163376-297x189.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-contrast-e1743521163376-120x76.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-contrast-e1743521163376-768x488.webp 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>The Details Matter</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Chris King says they concentrated on a few key elements of the Centerlock ring, the threading, and the backside’s knurling. These are arguably the most important aspects of the Centerlock lock ring design.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-pink-and-purp.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-pink-and-purp.webp\" alt=\"Chris King Centerlock Lockrings pink and purp\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-pink-and-purp.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-pink-and-purp-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-pink-and-purp-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-pink-and-purp-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-pink-and-purp-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-pink-and-purp-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>King’s “ultra-precise” threading will keep your lockring in place when installed and torqued to spec. And, the knurling is said to grab the rotor as it should, with a thin steel crush washer there to help the ring release when it’s time for maintenance.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-blue-closeup-e1743521233745.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"986\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-blue-closeup-e1743521233745.webp\" alt=\"Chris King Centerlock Lockrings blue closeup\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-blue-closeup-e1743521233745.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-blue-closeup-e1743521233745-297x229.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-blue-closeup-e1743521233745-120x92.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-blue-closeup-e1743521233745-768x592.webp 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The new Chris King Centerlock rings are made from CNC-machined aluminum, just like all your other favorite colorful King goodies. They include a steel crush washer, and sport the classic King laser-etched markings to match their headsets and hubs. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The new lock rings are available in all eleven of the current Chris King colors, plus Two-Tone Black &amp; Gold.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-torque.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-torque.webp\" alt=\"Chris King Centerlock Lockrings torque\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-torque.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-torque-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-torque-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-torque-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-torque-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-torque-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>“<em>King components stand out because we get all the little details right,</em>” said King Sales Director Greg Hudson, “<em>Standard lockrings have clumsy threads, and they come loose too easily. We precision-threaded ours, so they hold tight. We also gave extra attention to the knurling that grabs the rotor on the backside. There’s a lot of engineering in this one little component</em>.”</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-gun-metal.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-gun-metal.webp\" alt=\"Chris King Centerlock Lockrings gun metal\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-gun-metal.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-gun-metal-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-gun-metal-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-gun-metal-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-gun-metal-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-gun-metal-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>“<em>We expect many riders will want these to complement their hub colors,</em>” Hudson continued, “<em>or use them as contrast for headset and bottom bracket. It’s another way for riders to tie their bikes together with color. But we put a lot of energy into this design. It looks great, and it’s functionally better.</em>”</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Chris King Centerlock lock rings – Pricing &amp; Key Details</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-in-action.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-in-action.webp\" alt=\"Chris King Centerlock Lockrings in action\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-in-action.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-in-action-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-in-action-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-in-action-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-in-action-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Chris-King-Centerlock-Lockrings-in-action-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Retail price: $25 each (<em>per wheel</em>)</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Made in the USA</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Comes in 11 King Component matching colors</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Weight: 9 grams a piece</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>These little gems are available individually from authorized King retailers and directly from the sourse:</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"http://chrisking.com/\" target=\"_blank\">ChrisKing.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/boring-wheelset-chris-kings-new-anodized-centerlock-lock-rings-are-the-solution/\">Boring Wheelset? Chris King’s New Anodized Centerlock Lock Rings are the Solution</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"959ff0217e4d052a039673c7dd80f99b8cf12ca9d129c2d95114e45007e90cff","category":"Cycling"}